gomodel:SYNGO_662  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Localization of VGLUT3 on synaptic vesicles.\n\nFigure 4: electron microscopic postembedding immunogold labelings of VGLUT3 in CA1 hippocampal region. The presence of gold particles spatially related to synaptic vesicle membranes in the WT slices together with an absence of staining in VGLUT3 KO slices suggests that VGLUT3 is an integral protein of the SV membrane.\n\nFigure 6 demonstrates western blot analysis of SVs immunoisolated from WT mouse brains using VGAT or VGLUT3 antibodies after fractionation. The positive western blot signal in these fraction indicates that VGLUT3 is an integral protein of the SV membrane.. Experimental description: Figure 4. VGLUT3 and VGAT are associated with the same synaptic\nvesicles in wild-type mice, and VGLUT3 knockouts are devoid\nof VGLUT3 immunogold labeling.\nFor Figure 6 'Immunoisolation of synaptic vesicles Six mice were killed by decapitation, and whole-brain synaptic vesicles were isolated according to the protocol by Erickson et al. (1990).'" , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0030285 replaced by GO:0030672" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0755-5899" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0938-8534" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7351-8706" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3185-5709" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_662" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

